  "_comment": "A 6-frame sword swing built as an articulated RIG, not a stamp slid around. Each frame is a POSE: the back leg plants while the front leg lunges (weight shift), the torso leans, and the SWORD rotates about the hand (pivot [1,8]) through a real arc — anticipation (wind back) -> strike -> follow-through -> settle. The slash trails the blade on the action frames. This is the animation analogue of the sequencer scheduling parts on a grid: parts re-posed per frame, the swing carried by arbitrary-angle pivoted rotation.",
